source_text: Multiply this + 1 to the existing amount, adding all these multipliers together. So with a base of 3, and multipliers of 2 and 4, it would be 3 * (1 + 2 + 4) = 21

source_text: Multiply this + 1 to the existing amount, multiplying all these multipliers together. So with a base of 3, and multipliers of 2 and 4, it would be 3 * (1 + 2) * (1 + 4) = 45
